Package JavaHw_2

Class City

  • java.lang.Object
    • JavaHw_2.City
  • public class City
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a basic city and citizens Will at least have a city hall and one school City is created ground up by adding in more citizens and buildings after city hall and initial school

      • addPolice

        public void addPolice​(Police.Role role,
                      int id,
                      int age,
                      java.lang.String name,
                      java.lang.String phoneNumber,
                      double money,
                      java.lang.String buildingName)
               throws java.lang.Exception
        calls police constructor allows for the new police object to immediately be assigned to a building's occupant list, if the buildingName is not set to null always adds new police object to citizens list of City
        Parameters:
        role - police role, for police constructor
        id - police id, for police constructor and employee implementation
        age - person age, for constructor
        name - person name, for constructor
        phoneNumber - person's phone number, for constructor
        money - person's starting money, for constructor
        buildingName - name of building they should occupy, if one is desired when calling method
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - carries on the age constraint exception that can be thrown by police for age being under 18

      • addTeacher

        public void addTeacher​(Teacher.GradeLevel newLevel,
                       Teacher.TeachingCertification newCertification,
                       int newId,
                       int age,
                       java.lang.String name,
                       java.lang.String phoneNumber,
                       double money,
                       java.lang.String buildingName)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        calls teacher constructor allows for the new teacher object to immediately be assigned to a building's occupant list, if the buildingName is not set to null always adds new teacher object to citizens list of City
        Parameters:
        newLevel - for teacher constructor, the grade level that a teacher teaches; choices are in an enum: ELEMENTARY, MIDDLE, HIGH, UNIVERSITY
        newCertification - for teacher constructor, the certification that the teacher has, this determines pay. choices in an enum: UNDERGRADUATE, MASTERS, DOCTORATE
        newId - the teacher id, for teacher constructor and employee implementation
        age - the person's age, for constructor
        name - the person's name, for constructor
        phoneNumber - the person's phoneNumber, for constructor
        money - the person's starting money, for constructor
        buildingName - name of building they should occupy, if one is desired when calling the method
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if age is set below 18, carried from teacher constructor
